# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# CLIENT ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# SECURITY NOTICE:
# All client-side environment variables MUST be prefixed with "VITE_"
#
# The Vite build configuration only bakes specific, PUBLIC values into the
# client bundle. Server-side secrets (DATABASE_URL, SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY,
# SUPABASE_JWT_SECRET, STRIPE_SECRET_KEY, CLOUDFLARE_REALTIME_TOKEN, …) must
# NEVER be given a VITE_ prefix — they would ship to every browser.
#
# ✅ SAFE:   VITE_API_URL, VITE_SUPABASE_URL, VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
# ❌ UNSAFE: DATABASE_URL, SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY, any *_SECRET*
#
# See: client/src/test/vite-config.test.ts for security validation tests
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ─── Supabase (public values only) ──────────────────────────────────────
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
# Either the legacy anon key or the new publishable key works:
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key
# VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=sb_publishable_...

# ─── API ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000
VITE_WS_URL=ws://localhost:5000

# ─── Stripe (publishable key only) ──────────────────────────────────────
VITE_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=your_stripe_publishable_key_here

# ─── Community links ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
VITE_FACEBOOK_GROUP_URL=https://www.facebook.com/groups/your-group
VITE_DISCORD_URL=https://discord.com/invite/your-invite

# ─── Optional: MoQ relay for chat-type real-time data transport ──────────
# VITE_MOQ_RELAY_URL=https://relay.cloudflare.mediaoverquic.com
